title: Contributing to dendroNetwork
text: Fork package clone onto computer. haven’t done , recommend using usethis::create_from_github("RonaldVisser/dendroNetwork", fork = TRUE). Install development dependencies devtools::install_dev_deps(), make sure package passes R CMD check running devtools::check(). R CMD check doesn’t pass cleanly, ’s good idea ask help continuing. Create Git branch pull request (PR). recommend using usethis::pr_init("brief-description--change"). Make changes, commit git, create PR running usethis::pr_push(), following prompts browser. title PR briefly describe change. body PR contain Fixes #issue-number. user-facing changes, add bullet top NEWS.md (.e. just first header). Follow style described https://style.tidyverse.org/news.html.

title: dendroNetwork: how to use it
text: package aims make creation dendrochronological (provenance) networks easy possible. able make use options, assumed Cytoscape (Shannon et al. 2003) installed (https://cytoscape.org/). Cytoscape open source software platform independent provides easy visual access complex networks, including attributes nodes edges network (see Cytoscape-website information). data included package, namely Roman data published Hollstein (Hollstein 1980). first steps visualized flowchart , including community detection using either () Girvan-Newman algorithm (Girvan Newman 2002) Clique Percolation Method (Palla et al. 2005) clique sizes. methods explained well papers, wikipedia CPM Girvan-Newman algorithm. information dendrochronological data can found separate vignette.   large datasets tree-ring series see also vignette("large_datasets_communities") .
code: library(dendroNetwork) data(hol_rom) # 1 sim_table_hol <- sim_table(hol_rom) # 2 g_hol <- dendro_network(sim_table_hol) # 3 g_hol_gn <- gn_names(g_hol) # 4 g_hol_cpm <- clique_community_names(g_hol, k=3) # 4 hol_com_cpm_all <- find_all_cpm_com(g_hol) # 5 # plotting the graph in R plot(g_hol) # better readable version plot(g_hol, vertex.color="deepskyblue", vertex.size=15, vertex.frame.color="gray",      vertex.label.color="darkslategrey", vertex.label.cex=0.8, vertex.label.dist=2)

title: dendrochronological data
text: package dendroNetwork based using dendrochronological (tree-ring) data. data input creating networks uses data format used dplR (Bunn 2008). base format rwl-format described : https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/paleo/treering/treeinfo.txt. data can imported R using dplR::read.tucson("filename.rwl") . resulting dataframe series columns years rows, shown selection data one sample data sets dendroNetwork::hol_rom[400:410,1:4] : row names years tree rings dated, case years -103 -93, words 102 92 BCE (year 0 exist, mathematically). column headers identification names tree-ring series. values represent width tree ring millimeters. dendroNetwork written based measurements tree-ring widths, time series similar rwl-format can also used input. packages comes two sample data sets try package.

text: Dendrochronological site chronologies published earlier (Visser, n.d., 2021). (pre) Roman site chronologies date 520 BC AD 663 based material RING (full references source data can found supplementary data (Visser 2021). series named based location, species type standardisation example: ABC_Q1M ABC_Q1C consist material site ABC (Abcoude), species Q(uercus), chronology 1 standardisation C(ofecha) M(eans). See Visser(2021) explanation.

what: Community detection in very large datasets
title: Finding communities in large datasets
text: using larger datasets tree-ring series, calculating table similarities can take lot time, finding communities even . therefore recommended use parallel computing Clique Percolation: clique_community_names_par(network, k=3, n_core = 4). reduces amount time significantly. datasets clique_community_names() sufficiently fast smaller datasets clique_community_names_par() can even slower due parallelisation. Therefore, funtion clique_community_names() used initially slow, start using clique_community_names_par(). workflow similar described vignette("dendroNetwork"), minor changes: load network. compute similarities. find maximum clique size: igraph::clique_num(network) . detect communities clique size separately: com_cpm_k3 <- clique_community_names_par(network, k=3, n_core = 6). com_cpm_k4 <- clique_community_names_par(network, k=4, n_core = 6). maximum clique size. merge single data frame com_cpm_all <- rbind(com_cpm_k3,com_cpm_k4, com_cpm_k5,... ) . create table use cytoscape communities: com_cpm_all <- com_cpm_all |> dplyr::count(node, com_name) |> tidyr::spread(com_name, n) . Continue visualisation Cytoscape, see relevant section vignette("dendroNetwork") .

title: Create Networks of Dendrochronological Series using Pairwise Similarity
text: creating network R, possible visualize network using Cytoscape. main advantage visualisation Cytoscape easy, intuitive visual. addition, easy automate workflows Cytoscape R (using RCy3). purpose need start Cytoscape firstly. Cytoscape completely loaded, next steps can taken. network can now loaded Cytoscape visualisation: cyto_create_graph(g_hol, CPM_table = hol_com_cpm_all, GN_table = g_hol_gn) Styles visualisation can now generated. However, Cytoscape comes lot default styles can confusing. Therefore recommended use: cyto_clean_styles() session. can repeated possible clique sizes. find maximum clique size network, please use: igraph::clique_num(g_hol). automate : (3:igraph::clique_num(g_hol)) { cyto_create_cpm_style(g_hol, k=, com_k = g_hol_cpm)}. visualize styles using Girvan-Newman algorithm (GN): cyto_create_gn_style(g_hol) look something like Cytoscape: network Roman sitechronologies Girvan-Newman communities visualized.

title: Create Networks of Dendrochronological Series using Pairwise Similarity
text: using larger datasets tree-ring series, calculating table similarities can take lot time, finding communities even . therefore recommended use parallel computing Clique Percolation: clique_community_names_par(network, k=3, n_core = 4). reduces amount time significantly. datasets clique_community_names() sufficiently fast smaller datasets clique_community_names_par() can even slower due parallelisation. Therefore, function clique_community_names() used initially slow, start using clique_community_names_par(). See separate vignette .
